  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Workplace Health and Safety Officer/Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><ol><li>Implement the organization’s SHMS at office and site to manage risks and prevent accidents.</li><li>Initiates, review and implement the workplace safety, health and environment programs and initiatives.</li><li>Enforcement of safety standards in accordance with the Workplace Safety and Health Act and ensure familiarity with any statutory changes or updates.</li><li>Liaise with MOM and other relevant authorities on WSH-related matters as applicable.</li><li>Conduct training programs on workplace safety and health and inspections to ensure that all staff and/or subcontractors onsite abide by policies and standards.</li><li>Lead a team of WSH Co-ordinators to ensure strict compliance of procedures in statutory workplace, safety, health & environment requirements at sites and required premises.</li><li>Preparation and/or submission of MSRA, safety reports and necessary audits.</li><li>Assist the company in safety related certifications and awareness such as safety audits, ISO & Bizsafe audits, etc</li><li>Attend client/consultant safety meetings/weekly coordination meetings & technical meetings.</li><li>Lead investigation and maintain records for every first aid case, accident and near miss at the work site.</li><li>Conduct emergency drills periodically.</li><li>Any other ad hoc duties assigned by management.</li><li>For officer, must be a Singapore Registered Safety Officer/Workplace Safety & Health Officer with MOM.</li></ol>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
